node.text:
This week we are thrilled to be celebrating the 15th anniversary of ferm LIVING. What initially began as just our founder, Trine Andersen, a bold idea and ten wallpaper designs, has since grown into an established design brand that fuses a Scandinavian mindset with global skills and traditions. 

As ferm LIVING has grown over the years, one thing remains the same: our ambition to inspire people to create a home where they can be comfortably and authentically themselves – a home that embraces you just as you are.

node.text:
This year, Christmas may very well be a smaller, more intimate affair than usual. So now is the perfect opportunity to unleash your creative side with a beautiful, thoughtful table setting that will make your cherished guests feel extra welcome and appreciated while setting the tone for cosy holiday celebrations.

To see more, follow the link in our bio.

node.text: Learn how to make your very own Poppykalas Advent wreath together with Thilde, the founder and creative mind behind @Poppykalas, a Floral Design Studio based in Copenhagen. Her distinctive, pastel-hued creations often take untamed and unexpected forms, at once both delicate and extravagant. In this tutorial, she shares a step by step guide as to how you can create a fun and unique Advent decoration with the use of dried flowers and the Bowl Candle Holder from ferm LIVING.

node.title: Poppykalas: How to Make Your Own Advent Wreath

node.text: A talk between Trine Andersen, Founder and Creative Director of ferm LIVING, and Julie @vonsperling, a hospitality expert with 20 years of experience from the world's leading hotels. Held during 3daysofdesign at the Home of ferm LIVING in Copenhagen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on August 20, 2021. May be an image of furniture.

node.text: With room for personality, Sector is a modern take on a Mid-century shelving unit and is defined by its sturdy simplicity and classic combination of wood and brass. Available in various sizes, you can build a bespoke modular shelving unit for the livingroom to display favourite objects, or in the kitchen for storing mugs and jars.

node.text:
We have had the pleasure of visiting the talented @marielouise_hoestbo at her home in Copenhagen. Marie-Louise is a renowned Danish Architecture Specialist and the author of Secret Places: the architect’s guide to distinctive buildings in and around Copenhagen. Marie-Louise’s home, which also functions as her professional workspace, bears numerous signs of her profession, most discernibly in her extensive collection of architecture and design books, which take up two walls in each of the adjoining living rooms.
​
​Read the full story and see more of Marie-Louise's classic Østerbro apartment by following the link in bio.

node.text: No office is complete without a proper paper bin. Our sleek Rob Basket made in metal is a modern favourite that works perfectly as a storage solution for larger things in the office, such as paper rolls, or as a stylish paper bin. The asymmetric pattern of panels gives the basket a graphic expression, which seamlessly blends into any office decor.

node.text: As we're cooking favourite meals in the kitchen, it often turns into a big creative mess. Our yarn-dyed Hale Tea Towels are available in various colours and patterns and will surely help make cleaning a pleasure rather than a chore.

node.text: Whether your office space is your own, or you share it with someone else, the office should inspire deep reflection as well as creativity. Made from recycled casted aluminum, the Yama Pencil Holder features a rough, matte finish that contrasts its fluid and organic silhouette. With three different compartments in varying heights, the Yama Pencil Holder is ideal for storing all the stationery you use every day.

node.text: Make those last, balmy summer evenings more comfortable and cosy by adding warm lighting and soft textiles. Merging tradition with the contemporary, our Grand Cushions are made from a lovely mix of natural linen and cotton, and feature a confectionary of understated yet inspiring patterns and colour combinations to suit any mood or setting.

node.text: Late summer is upon us, and it is time to soak up those last warming rays of summer sun before autumn begins. Our Verso Jug is made from stoneware and recalls the classic shapes from traditional pottery. The delicate, feminine form features an artfully oversized handle, perfect for pouring a cold beverage on a warm August afternoon.

node.text: Any functional office space calls for a useful storage solution. With its sleek, powder-coated metal frame with reeded glass shelves, the Haze Bookcase perfectly merges industrial and modern design aesthetics. Use it in your office space to store books and papers or to stylishly display valued curio.

node.text: The Meridian Lamp presents a portable, dimmable lighting solution that works in a multitude of settings. With its intriguing, sculptural form, the Meridian Lamp is based on three simple geometric elements. Combined, the lamp presents a clean, modern expression. Use the Meridian Lamp in your office space whenever you're in need of some extra light to focus.

node.text: After a long, relaxing holiday, it is time to get back to all the exciting, new challenges that await. Any office space must have a proper desk and chair. Being a space for deep thought and new ideas, the chair in your office should be comfortable and inspire creativity, while the desk should have room for all your important papers, mood boards and stationery.

node.text:
Introducing Louisiana x ferm LIVING. 

Entering the collaboration with Louisiana, it was key that the design would echo the understated elegance that is the very essence of the iconic modern art museum. A significant trademark for Louisiana is their use of tall, whitewashed walls, exposed structures, wooden ceilings and deep-red tiled floors. It was their significant play with these contrasts in colours and materials that inspired the characteristic Louisiana x ferm LIVING fabric. The contrasts of the clean, classic lines together with the roundness of the Rico 2-seater and Lounge Chair makes a comfortably iconic design, which invites a moment of slowness and stillness into your home. ​Available at Louisiana, Louisiana.dk and our ferm LIVING Boutique. 
​
​Follow the link in bio to read the full story about the Louisiana x ferm LIVING collaboration.

With its intriguing, asymmetrical profile, the Level Side Table has a modern expression owing to its solitary geometric form. The table is suitable both for indoor and outdoor use, allowing you to create an outdoor summer living room where you can enjoy a delicious cup of afternoon coffee while relaxing with a good book. 
​
​Thank you to ​@catarinamira for sharing this lovely photo featuring our Level Side Table, Inlay Cup with Saucer, Linen Napkin and Flow Napkin Ring.
